Privacy tools blacklist and hot tips

  • Brave - guys, it's not about privacy, it's about money. Brave leak everything. They are highly popular only because there affiliate program and corrupt bloggers who want only money. evidence
  • Mobile phone - is not about your privacy. This is your collar. Use desktop with open source software for at least some privacy
  • ProtonMail - is privacy joke. They use hot descriptions about encryption to mislead you and control your data.
  • Free VPN - any free and paid vpn spy on you. You can use all of them, but be careful.
  • Proprietary software - forget about it. The best in this world is free. Use open source alternatives. This list is good place to start
  • os? - Use any not proprietary os. QubesOS is good choose, but better not to be like everyone. You can use any linux os as host + virtualization to create safe environments for your different tasks.
  • Signal - do you really think that messenger like telegram which request your mobile number and upload your contacts to there servers has something in common with privacy?
  • Bridgefy - the messenger promoted for mass protests, is a privacy disaster

firefox addons

I would advise people to be careful with plugins/extensions/add-ons. Add-ons are risky, they bring more attack surface, and you add yet another party you need to trust add-on developer. Before installing add-ons, think about the following: What does the add-on do and what is the impact of it? Who is the developer of this add-on? Is said add-on open source? Does the benefit of add-on outweigh the con of extra attack surface, and adding another party to trust.
